FBIS3-39206 "drweu030_j_94006" FBIS-WEU-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Liberal Factions Establish Parties BR1002151694 Rome LA REPUBBLICA in Italian 8 Feb 94 p 11 BR1002151694 Rome LA REPUBBLICA Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "Liberals Split -- A New Party Is Born"] [Text] Rome -- The latest split among the Liberals: At the end of the party congress, one faction has created the Center Union [UDC], with Stefano De Luca as its chairman, and another one has set up the Federation of Liberals. "De Luca and the UDC are aiming to become a satellite of Forza Italia," Raffaello Morelli, vice president of the Federation has said.
